+            align-items: centering, and **structured outputs** (JSON or schema-constrained responses via API features described later in this roadmap).\n\nThis topic catalogs **capability areas** at a high level. Exact availability depends on **model tier**, **surface** (chat vs API), and **plan**—always verify in current Anthropic docs before shipping a feature.\n\n### Language & documents\n\n- **Summarize** long articles, threads, or reports into bullets or executive briefs.\n- **Answer questions** about provided text (\"What are the risks in section 3?\").\n- **Draft and edit** emails, docs, marketing copy, and templates in a requested tone.\n- **Translate and simplify** content for different audiences while preserving meaning.\n- **Extract structure**—tables of requirements, action items, or entities—from messy notes.\n\n### Reasoning & analysis\n\n- **Break down problems** into steps (with stronger results when you ask for explicit reasoning).\n- **Compare options**—pros/cons, decision matrices, tradeoff narratives.\n- **Check logic** in arguments, specs, or policy drafts (not a substitute for domain experts on high-stakes calls).\n- **Extended thinking** (where enabled): models may spend additional internal effort on harder math, planning, or multi-constraint problems before answering.\n\n### Coding & technical work\n\n- **Explain code** in plain language or annotate unfamiliar libraries.\n- **Generate snippets**—functions, tests, SQL, config—in many languages.\n- **Debug** by reading stack traces and suggesting likely fixes (verify before merging).\n- **Refactor** for clarity or style when given constraints.\n- Developer tools like **Claude Code** extend this into repository-aware workflows (see Developer Platform topics).\n\n### Vision (multimodal)\n\nOn vision-capable models, Claude can **describe images**, read diagrams or screenshots, and answer questions about visual content you attach—useful for UI reviews, chart interpretation, or document photos.\n\n### Tools & integrations (developer-focused)\n\nThrough the API, Claude can participate in **tool-use loops**: your application exposes tools (or uses Anthropic-provided ones such as web search where available), Claude proposes tool calls, your code executes them, and results return to the model. This turns Claude from a language-only chatbot into an **agent component** inside your product.\n\n### What chat features add (product layer)\n\nConsumer and team products may include **Projects**, **Artifacts**, **memory**, and **connectors**—organizational layers on top of core model abilities. Those are covered under Claude.ai features, not repeated here.\n\n### Practical limits (preview)\n\nCapabilities are bounded by **context window size**, **model choice**, **latency**, and **policy/safety** filters. Overlong inputs truncate or must be chunked; sensitive requests may be refused. See **Limitations & Failure Modes** for the full picture.",
